    {
      "id": 0,
      "text": "My name is Priyanka Mali, and I am a Senior Software Engineer at Accenture, specializing in conversational AI and chatbot architecture, with a primary focus on Node.js and AWS. I hold the Claude Certified Architect — Foundations certification and have been actively using AI tools since 2022, giving me hands-on experience long before AI became mainstream. I currently run a 365 Days of AI series on Medium, where I learn AI from first principles and document the journey publicly. What makes the series different is that I don’t just write about concepts — I build real things alongside my learning. I have built a local AI chatbot using Node.js and Ollama, as well as a RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) system from scratch using nothing but a JSON file as the vector database — no paid APIs, no cloud, just code and experimentation. My writing style is curious, practical, and honest, more like a learner sharing notes than an expert lecturing. I write for people who use AI every day but want to better understand what actually happens under the hood. One of my recent milestones was having my Day 7 article published in Towards AI, one of the largest AI publications",
